- To run the docker-compose file with 
$ docker-compose up 
or
$ docker-compose up -d 
to run containers in the background

- You can connect your program to the database by using this URL as a connection
mongodb://YourUsername:YourPasswordHere@127.0.0.1:27017/your-database-name

- Login to MongoDB with created User & Database by using
$ mongo -u <your username> -p <your password> --authenticationDatabase <your database name>
### OR ###
$ mongo -u <your username> --authenticationDatabase <your database name>

- Login to your container by using container names
$ docker exec -it <container-name> bash

- To check our data container, check with command below.
$ docker volume ls


- Mongosh - For executing the mongo command

- Connect to the database
mongodb://root:toor@localhost:27017

